Search for Common Ground (SFCG) is an international non-profit organization that promotes the peaceful resolution of conflict. With headquarters in Washington, DC and Brussels, Belgium, Search’s mission is to transform how individuals, organizations, and governments deal with conflict—away from destructive approaches towards cooperative solutions. With more than 600 staff worldwide, Search implements projects in more than 30 countries across the globe. We are recruiting to fill the position below: Job Title: Monitoring and Evaluation Assistant Location: Maiduguri, Borno
Reports to: The Senior DMEL (SDMEL) Officer for the North East Position Summary Roles and Responsibilities Note: Job descriptions cannot be exhaustive, the position holder may be required to undertake other duties that are broadly in line with the above key duties.

